Between December 10 and December 15 2014, four ADHOC staff traveled to Indonesia (Lampoung province, Sumatra).
ADHOC staff learned 4 key strategic lessons which will be further studied and implemented in the Alternative Dispute Resolution work of ADHOC:
1.Integrate the use of internet in responding to people’s concerns and public conflicts.
2.Organize public forums for solving large scale conflicts between people.
3.Integrate conciliation and advocacy in case of a conflict between people and a company.
4.Help people representatives to participate in national public policy reform.